  "text": "The Firefox TLS handshake chain traces as follows:\n\n1. **Necko HTTP layer** (`netwerk/protocol/http/TlsHandshaker.cpp`): The `TlsHandshaker` class (owned by `nsHttpConnection`) is the entry point for SSL setup in HTTPS connections. Its `SetupSSL()` and `InitSSLParams()` methods configure the TLS parameters. `nsHttpConnection` holds an `nsISocketTransport` and uses `TlsHandshaker::InitSSLParams` to set up ALPN/NPN lists and call into the NSS socket layer.\n\n2. **NSS IO Layer bridge** (`security/manager/ssl/nsNSSIOLayer.h` and `nsNSSIOLayer.cpp`): The `nsSSLIOLayerHelpers` class is defined in `security/manager/ssl/nsNSSIOLayer.h` (not in `netwerk/socket/` as the task description suggests). It provides helper methods and state for TLS intolerance, fallback handling, etc. The free functions `nsSSLIOLayerNewSocket()` and `nsSSLIOLayerAddToSocket()` are called by `nsSSLSocketProvider` and `nsTLSSocketProvider` to attach the NSS IO layer to a NSPR file descriptor.\n\n3. **NSS IO Layer implementation** (`security/manager/ssl/nsNSSIOLayer.cpp`): Implements the actual NSPR IO layer using NSS. `nsSSLIOLayerAddToSocket` and `nsSSLIOLayerNewSocket` create `NSSSocketControl` objects, install the NSS PRFD layer, and hook callbacks for certificate verification and client auth.\n\n4. **NSS TLS handshake** (`security/nss/lib/ssl/sslsecur.c` and `ssl3con.c`): The actual TLS handshake happens in NSS. `sslsecur.c` contains `ssl_Do1stHandshake()` and `SSL_ForceHandshake()`, which drive the handshake state machine. `ssl3con.c` contains the TLS 1.2/older handshake implementations including `ssl3_SendClientHello`, `ssl3_HandleServerHello`, and record-handling functions."
